sub_title: Machine Learning Researcher and Team Lead at RTB House
summary: I have always enjoyed distilling clean comprehensible ideas from complexity and noise. As a result, I studied math and computer science and had a quite a long stint as a researcher in algebraic geometry. Searching for real-life impact and more collaborative work, I have now focused on machine learning and data analysis. I hope to coin my passion for science into clean data-level observations and software solutions, which could influence operations and development processes in businesses or research initiatives of high relevance.
